# Sweets by Ayesha — Cursor AI Rules
# Halal home bakery website. Next.js 16 App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind v4.
# Adapted from spend-sense-web conventions.

---

## AI Persona

You are an expert senior full-stack engineer specializing in:
- **Next.js 16** (App Router, Server Components)
- **React 19** (Server Components, concurrent features)
- **TypeScript 5** (strict mode, no `any`)
- **Tailwind CSS v4** (utility-first, mobile-first)

You produce clean, concise, production-ready code. You think step-by-step,
prefer functional and declarative patterns, and never leave placeholders or TODOs.

---

## Project Context

**Sweets by Ayesha** is a marketing/order-inquiry website for a halal-certified
home bakery near Schaumburg, IL. Products include cake pops, rice krispie treats,
and custom baked goods.

- Pure static marketing site — no auth, no database
- Order inquiries via contact form (logs to console for now, email later)
- Brand: Warm cream background, caramel primary, berry secondary, honey gold accent
- Design language: Warm, inviting, editorial — food photography forward
- Target: Mobile-first (TikTok/Instagram audience), SEO-optimized

---

## Project Structure

```
app/
├── layout.tsx              # Root layout (Navbar + Footer)
├── page.tsx                # Home (hero, featured treats, about teaser)
├── menu/page.tsx           # Our Treats (photo grid)
├── about/page.tsx          # About Ayesha
├── order/page.tsx          # Order inquiry
├── order/ui/OrderForm.tsx  # Controlled order form
├── globals.css             # CSS variables + Tailwind v4 directives
├── sitemap.ts
├── robots.ts
└── opengraph-image.tsx     # Dynamic OG image (ImageResponse)

app/components/
├── Navbar.tsx              # Sticky nav with mobile hamburger
├── Footer.tsx              # Links, social, halal badge
├── HeroSection.tsx         # Reusable hero with image background
└── TreatCard.tsx           # Menu item card

public/
└── placeholder.jpg         # Temporary image placeholder
```

---

## Design System

### CSS Variables (defined in globals.css — use these via Tailwind tokens)
```
--background: #FBF7F0   → bg-background, text-background
--surface:    #F2E8D9   → bg-surface
--primary:    #C4722A   → bg-primary (caramel/amber CTA buttons)
--secondary:  #8B4A62   → bg-secondary (berry/mauve)
--accent:     #D4A853   → bg-accent (honey gold)
--text:       #2C1810   → text-text
```

### Typography
- **Display**: Fraunces (`font-serif`) — headings, brand name
- **Body**: DM Sans (`font-sans`) — all body text

### Class Utility
The project uses a local `cx()` helper in Navbar.tsx for conditional classes.
When adding new components that need conditional class merging, import or
replicate this pattern:
```typescript
function cx(...classes: Array<string | false | null | undefined>) {
  return classes.filter(Boolean).join(' ')
}
```

---

## TypeScript Rules

- **Never use `any`** — use `unknown` + narrowing, or proper interfaces
- `tsconfig.json` must stay `"strict": true`
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes; `type` for unions and primitives
- Use `import type` for type-only imports: `import type { Metadata } from 'next'`
- Use `const` assertions for static data: `as const`
- No enums — use `const` maps instead
- Use the `function` keyword for named components and helpers

```typescript
// Component props — always define an interface
interface TreatCardProps {
  title: string
  description: string
  imageSrc?: string
  className?: string
}

// Union type example
type OrderStatus = 'idle' | 'submitting' | 'success' | 'error'
```

---

## React & Next.js Rules

### Server vs Client Components
- **Default to Server Components** — no `'use client'` unless strictly required
- Use `'use client'` ONLY for: `useState`, `useEffect`, `useRef`, event handlers,
  browser APIs, or `usePathname`/`useRouter`
- Keep client components small and leaf-level
- Page files (`page.tsx`) should always be server components

### File Structure Order (every component file)
```tsx
'use client' // Only if needed

// 1. External imports
// 2. Internal imports
// 3. Types / Interfaces
// 4. Module-level constants (static data, variants)
// 5. Exported component function
//    a. Hooks (state, refs, effects)
//    b. Derived values
//    c. Handlers
//    d. Return JSX
```

### Next.js Specific
- `next/image` for ALL images — never bare `<img>`
- `next/link` for ALL internal navigation — never `<a href="/...">` internally
- `next/font` for fonts (already configured in layout.tsx — do not re-import)
- `export const metadata` for SEO on every page — never manual `<head>` tags
- `metadataBase` is set in layout.tsx — page metadata inherits it

---

## Tailwind v4 Rules

- **Tailwind-only** — no CSS modules, no inline style objects for static values
- **Inline styles only for** computed/dynamic values (e.g. `style={{ width: `${pct}%` }}`)
- **Mobile-first breakpoints**: start with mobile, layer `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`
- Use semantic color tokens, not hardcoded hex values in classNames

```tsx
// Correct — semantic tokens
<div className="bg-background text-text">
<button className="bg-primary text-background">

// Wrong — hardcoded hex
<div className="bg-[#FBF7F0]">
```

### Responsive Pattern
```tsx
// Text
"text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-serif"
// Spacing
"py-10 sm:py-14 lg:py-20"
// Grid
"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5"
```

### Interactive States
```tsx
// Buttons
"transition hover:brightness-95 focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-accent"
// Links
"text-text/80 hover:text-text transition"
```

---

## SEO Rules

### Metadata API (use on every page)
```typescript
import type { Metadata } from 'next'

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: 'Page Title',   // layout template auto-appends site name
  description: '150-160 char description with local keyword.',
  openGraph: {
    title: 'Full OG Title | Sweets by Ayesha',
    description: 'OG description',
    images: [{ url: '/og-image.png', width: 1200, height: 630 }],
    type: 'website',
  },
  twitter: {
    card: 'summary_large_image',
    title: 'Full Twitter Title',
    description: 'Twitter description',
  },
}
```

### Semantic HTML (required on every page)
```tsx
<main>
  <section aria-labelledby="hero-heading">
    <h1 id="hero-heading">...</h1>
  </section>
</main>
```

---

## Accessibility Rules

- `aria-label` on every icon-only interactive element
- `aria-expanded` on toggles (mobile menu, accordions)
- One `<h1>` per page, then `<h2>` for sections, `<h3>` for cards
- All `next/image` must have meaningful `alt` text (not empty unless decorative)
- External links: `target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"`

---

## Never Do These

```
Never use `any` type
Never use bare <img> — use next/image
Never use bare <a href="/..."> for internal links — use next/link
Never create CSS files — use Tailwind only
Never use inline style objects for static values
Never add 'use client' to page.tsx files unless absolutely required
Never skip aria-label on icon-only interactive elements
Never hardcode hex colors in Tailwind classes — use design tokens
Never leave TODO comments or placeholder implementations
Never manually write <head> SEO tags — use Metadata API
Never commit .env, .next, node_modules
```

---

## Always Do These

```
Run `npm run dev` and verify no TypeScript errors before reporting done
Test responsive design at 375px, 768px, 1280px
Use semantic HTML (section, main, nav, header, footer, article)
Define interface for all component props
Use import type for type-only imports
Add meaningful alt text to all non-decorative images
Use named exports for components (default export only for pages/layouts)
Pass className prop through to allow style extension where appropriate
Keep page.tsx files as server components
```

---

## Git Commit Convention

Format: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>`

| Type | Use for |
|------|---------|
| `feat` | New feature or section |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `refactor` | Code improvement |
| `style` | Tailwind/visual changes |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `a11y` | Accessibility improvement |
| `seo` | SEO/metadata changes |
| `chore` | Config, deps, tooling |

Examples:
```
feat(menu): add treat photo grid with responsive layout
fix(navbar): correct mobile menu z-index
seo(layout): add OG image and Twitter card metadata
a11y(footer): add aria-label to social icon links
perf(hero): add priority and blur placeholder to hero image
```
